<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active from late spring to mid-summer and range in total length 15-18 mm and 6-7.5 mm in maximum width. Individuals are readily attracted to artificial lights at night, but are also active during the day while crawling and mating on dead tree surfaces. In Hong Kong, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera indica" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Derris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Derris" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Derris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. have been reported as food plants for the larvae of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Other host plants include 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Derris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Derris trifoliata" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="trifoliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Derris trifoliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Hevea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hevea brasiliensis" order="Geraniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Hevea brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera indica" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Shorea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Shorea" order="Guttiferales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Shorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Terminalia</emphasis>
sp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Lin, M-Y" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B89" refString="Lin, M-Y, Yang, X-K, 2019. Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae." year="2019">Lin and Yang 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
